<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFBFFBAFC95985C6C15798D" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC95985C6D44790F" blockId="22.[831,1437,1047,1260]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC95985C6ABD7951" bold="true" box="[831,944,1048,1072]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Remarks:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFBFFBAFBF1985C6DCB794E" baseAuthorityName="D'ORBIGNY" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1115,1222,1048,1071]" class="Nodosariata" family="Vaginulinidae" genus="Neoflabellina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaginulinida" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFBF1985C6DCB794E" box="[1115,1222,1048,1071]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">N. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a narrow test, fewer coiled chambers and higher sutures with irregularly shaped loops.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC9598326C15798D" blockId="22.[831,1437,1047,1260]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC9598326D7079EF" bold="true" box="[831,1149,1142,1166]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Paleocene by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) and LUGER (1985). It is rarely found in the Maastrichtian and floody in the Paleocene of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
